                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1011">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.W931/215.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-07-17T09:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1913—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>333. I have taken charge of the Embassy. The Ambassador sails today for the
                    United States via Habana in pursuance of the Department’s instructions.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d1011fn1">Not printed.</note> If arrangements can be made with
                    the quarantine authorities he will proceed thence to Washington via Key
                    West.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
